OL,6,F"We have a proud tradition of free
OL,7,Fspeech and I think it just shows -
OL,8,Fwhether it's the SNP or Labour - these
OL,9,Fare the wrong set of priorities for
OL,10,Fthe country," he said.
OL,12,FWhen pressed if he supports Rowling's
OL,13,Fapproach, Mr Sunak replied: "It's not
OL,14,Fright for me to comment on police
OL,15,Fmatters, individual matters, but what
OL,16,FI do support very strongly are
OL,17,Fpeople's right to free speech" but
OL,18,Fadded that "nobody should be
OL,19,Fcriminalised for saying common sense
OL,20,Fthings about biological sex".
